Tonight I was going to dine at a restaurant which I have a gift certificate
for. The gift certificate is for $25.

At the restaurant when I presented the gift certificate, I was told that the
gift certificates were no longer being honored. Apparently the restaurant
got new owners within the last few weeks and they were not honoring the
former issued gift certificates.

I was under the impression that when one bought a business, unless there was
a bankruptcy, the new owners aquired the obligations of the old owners.
This business was operating in the same location under the same name. I
spoke with the new owner and asked him if the old owners filed bankruptcy.
He indicated no--it was just an &quot;asset sale.&quot;

Is this legitimate?

FWIW, the business is Petralla's Italian Cafe in Pensacola, FL.

Tony

