I think the question really depends on whether they purchased the
parts of the business or they purchased the business. I believe that
even with the same business name on the outside an argument could
still be made that this is a new business if the paperwork is handled
properly in the sale.

I would also question whether &quot;terms and conditions may change at any
time&quot; is valid. It seems to me that a term such as this is unfair and
may be unenforceable. After all, how can you have agreement on terms
that do not yet exist?

In the end, whether it is legal or not is rarely an issue. A company
will make a decision based on what they want to do. Whether it is a
$25 certificate or a $10,000 contract.

My best suggestion is file a BBB complaint and an attorney general
complaint against the company and leave it at that.

</POST>



