and we probably will not know this until after such time as we receive
discovery from the appropriate parties. If we have reason to believe
the arguement is weak we should not proceed with a suit against the
party where the arguement is weak. If we find out later the arguement
is weak we should dismiss the case against that party for which the
case is weak.

I also believe that we should be proactive and attempt to determine
liability prior to filing a lawsuit against either party, however, my
past experience has shown that most people are not willing to provide
any information until they are required to do so by law.

